title.narrative: OUTPUT 4.1 NUTRITION ENABLING ENVIROMENT

description.narrative: By 2024, Gaps in laws, policies, strategies and guidelines are identified, closed and progressively implemented and monitored in line with international norms and standards., which contributes to Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition In Early Childhood (Covid), Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, Significantly more children under five, adolescents and women of childbearing age access and utilize proven direct nutrition interventions and practice appropriate nutrition behaviors that prevent stunting and other manifestations of malnutrition in both development and humanitarian conditions.

description.narrative: The Liberian Government began developing a National Multisectoral Costed Plan of Action for Nutrition (NMCPAN) as part of its Pro-Poor Agenda for Prosperity and Development (PAPD) commitment to reducing stunting. The Plan is being costed. The 15 nutrition indicators included in the Health Management System (HMIS) were added to Ministry of Health (MoH) national data verification (the national data quality assurance platform). The available budget to promote both dietary diversity in children aged 6–23 months and exclusive breastfeeding (by eliminating water/fluids) comes from the working towards improving nutrition at scale multi-year pool fund, not from the public sector. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
